    <h2 class="t-text-2xl t-font-bold t-mb-2">Your rights under the Australian Consumer Law</h2>
    {% comment %} <span class="t-text-sm t-text-gray-600 t-block t-mb-6">December 19 2024 5:40am</span> {% endcomment %}

    <div class="t-space-y-4 t-text-[15px] t-leading-relaxed t-font-sans">
      <p>Sheldon and Hammond Pty Limited (S&amp;H) is the Australian distributor of Osprey Packs, Inc.</p>
      <p>
        Our goods come with guarantees that cannot be excluded under the Australian Consumer Law. You are entitled to a
        replacement or refund for a major failure and compensation for any other reasonably foreseeable loss or damage.
        You are also entitled to have the goods repaired or replaced if the goods fail to be of acceptable quality and
        the failure does not amount to a major failure.
      </p>
      <p>
        These rights (known as consumer guarantees) are in addition to the manufacturer's warranty which are referred to
        as the All Mighty Guarantee (see below). A change of mind does not qualify as a consumer guarantee.
      </p>
      <p>
        S&amp;H will require satisfactory proof of purchase before providing a remedy under the consumer guarantees.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you purchase an Osprey product from us through our online store and you believe your product is faulty or
        defective, please complete the claim
        <a class="t-font-bold" href="http://www.ospreyaustralia.com.au/pages/almighty-guarantee-form">form</a>. To
        assist with your claim please provide a detailed description of the defect (including photos) when completing
        the form.
      </p>
      <p>
        S&amp;H will respond to your warranty claim and may request for more information (if needed) and the next steps
        (which may include requiring you to return the product to S&amp;H for an assessment). Before determining the
        remedy you are entitled to, in some cases we may need to send the item to Osprey for an assessment to confirm
        the problem.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you are asked to return the product, S&amp;H will pay for the cost of the postage from an Australian address
        to S&amp;H. You are responsible for packaging the product to prevent it from further damage during transit.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you have purchased an Osprey product from a retailer and you believe your product is faulty or defective,
        please contact that retailer directly.
      </p>
    </div>
