      <p>
        <span class="t-font-bold">4. Scope of AMG:</span> This AMG guarantee covers all defects in materials and
        workmanship under normal use during the guarantee period. During the AMG period, S&H will repair or replace, at
        no charge, products or parts of a product that prove defective because of improper material or workmanship,
        under normal use and maintenance.
      </p>
      <p>
        If Osprey in its or S&H's sole discretion, choose to repair the product then we will exercise our discretion to
        determine the extent of the repair work and the repairer of that work. Osprey, S&H and any third party that is
        engaged to perform the repair work cannot guarantee that upon completion of the repair work that the product
        will look identical to the product that you first received when you purchased the product. The intention of any
        repair work is to enable the product to be of acceptable quality and fit for its intended purpose.
      </p>

      <p>
        <span class="t-font-bold">5. What is not covered:</span> The AMG guarantee doesn’t cover the following types of
        damage or wear. This means S&H won’t replace or repair your product at our cost:
      </p>
      <ul class="t-list-disc t-ml-6 t-space-y-2">
        <li>
          <span class="t-font-bold">Wear and tear</span> – If your pack is showing signs of cosmetic aging (e.g.
          discolouration, logo peeling) or signs of use from regular adventures (e.g. fraying, punctures, holes,
          abrasions), then it will not be covered under the AMG. These are considered normal wear and tear. If your pack
          is functional, then it is not a defect in materials or workmanship.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="t-font-bold">Delamination (e.g. peeling/flaking)</span> – If you store your pack in damp
          conditions, use it in wet weather or store wet/damp items in your pack then this can cause delamination. If
          your pack shows signs of bubbling, peeling, flaking, cracking or loss of adhesion between the fabric layers
          then it is considered to be wear related and will not covered under the AMG.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="t-font-bold">Airline/Travel Damage</span> – If your pack is damaged whilst you are in transit due
          to the way in which the pack was handled, then this is not covered under the AMG. You will need to make a
          claim with the airline, travel operator or your insurer in that instance.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="t-font-bold">Animal Damage</span> – If your pack is damaged (intentionally or incidentally) by
          any animal (including rodents), such damage will not be covered by the AMG.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p><span class="t-font-bold">6. AMG Guarantee:</span> If there is a defect covered by this guarantee:</p>
